<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1952,2013]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1952,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Remarks.</emphasis>
The original description and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Asahina" authorityYear="1997" box="[822,981,1953,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamica">
<emphasis box="[822,981,1953,1976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">D. vietnamica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are inadequate. The 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1267,1953,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">type</typeStatus>
series consists of the 
<typeStatus box="[223,321,1988,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">holotype</typeStatus>
and one male 
<typeStatus box="[486,585,1989,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">paratype</typeStatus>
, both collected at “Ban A Chia, Hung Nga, Muong Lay, 
<collectingRegion box="[1224,1328,1988,2013]" country="Vietnam" name="Lai Chau" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Lai Chau</collectingRegion>
Prov” on the 8th of 
<date box="[268,383,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="1995-05">May 1995</date>
(Asahina 1997). Poor quality illustrations are given of the head and thorax and of the end of the abdomen; it is not stated whether the illustrations were made from the 
<typeStatus box="[1007,1105,188,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">holotype</typeStatus>
or the 
<typeStatus box="[1189,1285,189,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">paratype</typeStatus>
or both. The third author had already searched for these specimens in the National Museum of Nature and Science, 
<collectingRegion box="[1358,1432,223,248]" country="Japan" name="Tokyo" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Tokyo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,261,284]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Japan</collectingCountry>
, where they are supposed to be deposited, but could only find one specimen, with the correct date, and labelled “ 
<typeStatus box="[261,365,296,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">paratype</typeStatus>
”; he made sketches of the anal appendages (
<figureCitation box="[890,1022,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1859,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Drepanosticta vietnamica paratype: (17) head and thorax; (18) anal appendages, lateral view; (19) left cercus, dorsal view; (20) left paraproct,oblique dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1154486/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Figs 18–20</figureCitation>
) and a photograph of the head and thorax (
<figureCitation box="[240,326,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1859,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Drepanosticta vietnamica paratype: (17) head and thorax; (18) anal appendages, lateral view; (19) left cercus, dorsal view; (20) left paraproct,oblique dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1154486/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). The anal appendages of the 
<typeStatus box="[673,769,333,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">paratype</typeStatus>
differ quite significantly from the illustrations in Asahina (1997). Asahina’s (1997: 108) figure 2 (drawn from the right hand side) appears to show a ventral subapical flap on the cerci, not visible in lateral view in 
<figureCitation box="[592,673,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1859,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Drepanosticta vietnamica paratype: (17) head and thorax; (18) anal appendages, lateral view; (19) left cercus, dorsal view; (20) left paraproct,oblique dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1154486/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
here (drawn from the left hand side), instead only a small rounded interior flap is visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[578,662,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1859,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,1054,1838]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Drepanosticta vietnamica paratype: (17) head and thorax; (18) anal appendages, lateral view; (19) left cercus, dorsal view; (20) left paraproct,oblique dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1154486/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). This difference raises doubts either over the accuracy of Asahina’s illustration or over whether the 
<typeStatus box="[516,612,477,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">paratype</typeStatus>
actually belongs to the same species as the 
<typeStatus box="[1122,1224,476,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">holotype</typeStatus>
. However, since it seems unlikely that, even in the last stages of his career, Asahina would have mixed two species with anal appendages as different as the two sets of illustrations suggest, we suppose that it is more likely that Asahina’s illustrations are inaccurate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
